About
==========================

PyColors is a Python module that makes text coloring easier to do.

Example
==========================

#Linux
import PyColors

a = PyColors.linux()
b = a.color(text="This is the text that will be displayed", color='red', highlight='blue', other='bold')
print b

#Windows
import PyColors
	
a = PyColors.windows()
a.color(background="blue", textcolor='red')

#This will set the universal color to what ever you want, the windows class is not as useful as the linux class. 
